January 13, 2026
HOUSE BILL No. 1254
_____
DIGEST OF HB 1254 (Updated January 13, 2026 11:22 am - DI 147)
Citations Affected: IC 25-13; IC 25-14; IC 25-34.5.
Synopsis: Various dental matters; respiratory care. Amends the
educational requirements for dental hygienists. Amends the
requirements for administration of nitrous oxide by a dental hygienist.
Allows the state board of dentistry to establish additional requirements
for an applicant who has failed the licensure examination at least three
times. Amends the licensure and temporary permit requirements for
respiratory care practitioners.
Effective: July 1, 2026.
Goss-Reaves
January 5, 2026, read first time and referred to Committee on Public Health.
January 13, 2026, amended, reported — Do Pass.
HB 1254—LS 6889/DI 148

